### Process by Which an Individual Gains Access to a Computer System

The term "logon" redirects here. It's crucial to distinguish this from [Logone](/Logone_(disambiguation)), which, frankly, sounds like a particularly dull brand of furniture polish.

And yes, "logout" also redirects here. For those of you who found yourselves inexplicably drawn to a film titled [Logout (film)](/Logout_(film)), this is not that. This is about the mundane act of disengaging from a digital space. For any other permutations of this concept, consult [Login (disambiguation)](/Login_(disambiguation)).

If you're attempting to navigate the labyrinthine corridors of Wikipedia itself, the correct incantation is [Special:UserLogin](/Special:UserLogin). To depart from its digital embrace, you'll employ [Special:UserLogout](/Special:UserLogout). Try to keep up.

